
Active Directory Attack Scenarios

Overview

This repository contains a collection of attack scenarios executed against the DarkForest Active Directory environment.

The purpose is to validate the detection capabilities of the Splunk dashboards developed for the DarkForest SOC homelab by generating realistic Windows, Active Directory and OpenSSH events.

Each scenario focuses on a different phase of an intrusion, from initial access to Active Directory account manipulation.

⸻

Lab Infrastructure

Machine	Role
Debian 13 (Exegol)	Attacker
DC1	Windows Server 2022 Domain Controller
Splunk Enterprise	SIEM
OpenSSH Server	Remote Administration

⸻

Detection Coverage

The scenarios populate several dashboards including:

* Authentication Activity
* SSH Activity
* PowerShell Activity
* Sysmon Monitoring
* LDAP Activity
* Account Management

⸻

Scenario 001 – SSH Brute Force

Objective

Simulate an attacker attempting to obtain access to the Domain Controller through repeated SSH authentication attempts.

Attack Flow

Attacker
      │
      ▼
SSH Brute Force
      │
      ▼
Multiple Failed Passwords
      │
      ▼
Successful Authentication

Tool

* Hydra

Example Command

hydra -l Administrateur -P passwords.txt ssh://10.10.6.1

Expected Detection

Authentication Activity

* Failed SSH Logons
* Successful SSH Logons
* Top SSH Source IPs

MITRE ATT&CK

* T1110.001 – Password Guessing
* T1078 – Valid Accounts
* T1021.004 – SSH

⸻

Scenario 002 – Host Discovery

Objective

Once authenticated through SSH, perform basic host enumeration.

Commands

whoami
hostname
echo %COMPUTERNAME%
ipconfig
systeminfo
whoami /groups
net user
net user Administrateur
net localgroup Administrators
quser

Expected Detection

SSH Activity

* Successful SSH Login

Sysmon Monitoring

* Process Creation Timeline
* Top Process
* Suspicious Process

MITRE ATT&CK

* T1082 – System Information Discovery
* T1033 – System Owner Discovery
* T1069 – Permission Groups Discovery

⸻

Scenario 003 – Active Directory Enumeration

Objective

Enumerate Active Directory objects using the ActiveDirectory PowerShell module.

Commands

Import-Module ActiveDirectory
Get-ADDomain
Get-ADForest
Get-ADUser -Filter *
Get-ADComputer -Filter *
Get-ADGroup -Filter *
Get-ADOrganizationalUnit -Filter *
Get-ADGroupMember "Domain Admins"
Get-ADDefaultDomainPasswordPolicy

Expected Detection

PowerShell Activity

* PowerShell execution
* Suspicious AD cmdlets

Sysmon Monitoring

* PowerShell process creation
* Command line logging

MITRE ATT&CK

* T1087 – Account Discovery
* T1069 – Permission Groups Discovery
* T1482 – Domain Trust Discovery

⸻

Scenario 004 – Active Directory Account Management

Objective

Generate administrative Active Directory events by creating, modifying and deleting a test user.

The account used throughout this scenario is:

John Doe
Username : jdoe

⸻

Step 1 – Create User

New-ADUser `
-Name "John Doe" `
-GivenName "John" `
-Surname "Doe" `
-SamAccountName jdoe `
-UserPrincipalName jdoe@pale.forest `
-AccountPassword (ConvertTo-SecureString "P@ssw0rd123!" -AsPlainText -Force) `
-Enabled $true

Expected Event ID

* 4720 – User Account Created

⸻

Step 2 – Add User to Domain Admins

Add-ADGroupMember `
-Identity "Domain Admins" `
-Members jdoe

Expected Event IDs

* 4728
* 4732
* 4756

⸻

Step 3 – Remove User from Domain Admins

Remove-ADGroupMember `
-Identity "Domain Admins" `
-Members jdoe `
-Confirm:$false

Expected Event IDs

* 4729
* 4733
* 4757

⸻

Step 4 – Delete User

Remove-ADUser jdoe -Confirm:$false

Expected Event ID

* 4726 – User Account Deleted

⸻

Expected Detection

Account Management Dashboard

* Account Creation
* Privileged Group Membership Changes
* Account Deletion

MITRE ATT&CK

* T1098 – Account Manipulation

⸻

